Package: cmmr
Type: Package
Title: modelling of Covariance Matrices for longitudinal data with Multiple Responses using 'Armadillo' and S4
Version: 0.1.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Yi", "Pan", email = "ypan1988@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Jianxin", "Pan", email = "Jianxin.Pan@manchester.ac.uk",
                  role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Yi Pan <ypan1988@gmail.com>
Description: Modelling the covariance matrices of multivariate longitudinal data
    with multiple responses. The models and their components are represented
    using S4 classes and methods. The core computational algorithms are
    implemented using the 'Armadillo' C++ library for numerical linear algebra
    and 'RcppArmadillo' glue.
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: TRUE
SystemRequirements: C++11
Imports: jmcm (>= 0.1.7.0), Rcpp (>= 0.12.14)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
